# Overview
- Vampire Reputation is misplaced. Not all are so decidedly Evil.
- House Darius' Vampiric Nature is Secret
- Careful Reproduction.
- Sustain Their Lives And Wellbeing.

# Main Purposes & Goals
- House Ophelia first and foremost seeks to create a family that can withstand the test of time- which they already have.
- House Darius aims to keep its own house alive, even if Ophelia falls.
- They aim to maintain this ability to withstand the seemingly endless cycles that await, having withstood even the darkest periods.
- Protect themselves from Mortal aims.
- Feed carefully, seek out willing food sources.
- They also seem keen to disappear certain criminal elements where possible.

# Leadership & Membership
In Kudak Valley, the Cadet-House Darius looks to maintain its foothold as a refuge for Vampires, sending abroad those who need an escape. The Patriarch is Vahid Darius, and has been the patriarch for some five centuries, taking to the throne after his father Kazem left for the embrace of the Vampire Goddess Lilith, a God-In-Waiting.

Vampires are often brought into House Darius whether they like it or not. Darius takes a ruthless approach into bringing in new members, as those waifs and strays are often troublesome. New vampires can cause untold damage, while the more veteran members can slip away with ease, and are generally better at hiding. Those who do not comply are torn to shreds quickly. Few non-vampires have House Ophelia and their Cadets trust, for understandable reasons.

Those who do, are of a particular bunch- finding nobility in House Ophelia's goals.

# Locations
In the Kudak Valley, House Darius operates out of the Darius Estate, a large Mansion house built along the Kudak River. It is a heavily fortified place of rest for weary Vampires, and anyone else who can finagle a way into the place. Such darker things are kept secret even within, and guests are rarely bid entry. Invitations are extremely rare, and the Guards are notoriously terrifying.

The Darius Estate features a large shaded orchard, and a number of ornate gardens designed to entrap shade and shadow. Beneath the estate lays a number of tunnels, to ferret Vampires to safety.

# Publicity & Reputation
To the outside in, House Darius is known for its Banking establishments. After all, the Kudak Valley is rife with merchants, traders and the like. And with Ophelia running Banks & Similar venues, House Darius' Casinos are cashcows and a safe cover. Some branches exist outside of the Kudak Valley, but they largely have the lion's share of business within the Valley. They also help prop up and support other smaller town banks and so on, understanding the value of trusted, local banks.

# Founding & Past History
Founded by Vahid Darius

# Adversaries & Rivals
The House has been around for many, many centuries longer than a number of upstarts, and have a greater understanding of the stakes. They're also wary of the Scarlet Legion.

Their biggest enemy is the Tireless Cathedral, a Holy Order of Vampires who believe their superiority is the best course action, creating a pantheon of Vampiric Gods to bring them forth from the Gods-In-Waiting and stake their claim across Newol. This would drastically upset the balance. It is said they have ancient connections with grand evils, and manipulate the world to their whims. It isn't uncommon for people to disappear in such huge quantities as the Tireless Cathedral travel in groups. They live a hedonistic and pleasurable lifestyle, and engage with the strong and intelligent, longing to turn them to their cause.
